        "title": "Make a SQL query with unknown number of ANDs",
        "body": "<p>Imagine I would like to search my database for one or a combination of fields. Now I do not know how many of these fields I have. So I made a function which takes them all as argument but empty Strings for the ones which are not applicable (or 0 for ints)<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>findSometing(int serial, String att1, String att2, String att3)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Now when I'm making the query <code>SELECT * FROM TableName WHERE<\/code> I cannot determine where to put my <code>AND<\/code> commands. Does anyone have a good solution to this problem? I can do it with a lot of if statements but thats messy. \nJust to add I HAVE to use JDBC. <\/p>\n",
